# CureLink — Project Overview

**CureLink** is a full-stack **healthcare appointment management platform** that connects **Patients**, **Doctors**, and **Admins** through a unified web application.

---

## 🏗️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| **Frontend** | React (Vite) + Axios |
| **Backend** | Express.js (Node.js) |
| **Database** | MongoDB (Mongoose ODM) |
| **Auth** | JWT (HTTP-only cookies) + bcrypt |
| **Notifications** | Firebase |
| **Deployment** | Frontend → Vercel, Backend → Railway |

---

## 👥 Three User Roles

### 1. 🩺 Patient
- Register/login with email & password
- Browse available doctors (by specialization)
- Book appointments by selecting a doctor, date, and available time slot
- View upcoming & past appointments
- View medical records and prescriptions written by doctors
- Receive medicine reminders
- Get notifications (appointment confirmations, reminders, system alerts)

### 2. 👨‍⚕️ Doctor
- Login with credentials (account created by Admin)
- Set **availability** — specific dates with time slots (e.g., 10:00 AM – 10:30 AM)
- View patient appointments (incoming bookings)
- Update appointment status (confirm, complete, cancel)
- Write **medical records** after consultations:
  - Diagnosis & symptoms
  - Prescriptions (medicine name, dosage, timing, duration)
- View calendar of scheduled appointments

### 3. 🛡️ Admin
- Dedicated admin login
- **Doctor management**: Create, update, and delete doctor profiles (including specialization & experience)
- **User management**: View all users, delete user accounts
- **Appointment oversight**: View all appointments across the platform, filter by status/doctor/patient, update or cancel any appointment
- **Platform statistics dashboard**: Total doctors, patients, appointments, today's appointments, pending/completed/cancelled counts
- **Activity logs**: Track all admin actions (created doctor, deleted user, cancelled appointment, etc.) and platform-wide activity (patient registrations, appointment bookings)

